args:
(Tobias still seeks people's happiness,
even with his own life in the balance.
Surely such a heart cannot have been
stained with darkness.)

(He cannot be a heretic. He CANNOT.
But I'll need to find proof of such before
his trial If I am to... Ah, excellent.
The villagers have arrived!)
Listen to me, all of you!
Pray spare a moment and hear my words,\nfor I seek to aid Paladyn Tobias!
...Well, girly? Care to explain what you're\ndoin' here when it was your own Church\nwhat up and took him away?
Tobias is currently being tried as a heretic\nby the Church for harming a dragon.
But I cannot imagine him doing such\nan act without just cause.
I MUST learn of what happened here,\nand you are the only ones who can tell me.
Soft, little one. Soft. Talk to me.\nWhy do you say this is your fault?
I will explain that on her behalf.
Don't be a fool! You can't trust this one—\nshe's from the Church!
And yet she appears genuine\nin her desire to help Tobias.
Pray forgive my people their impudence.\nI will tell you what you wish to know.
I'll tell you all about that day...
Yes. She's not been seen since yesterday.
Please, you must help me find her!
We Paladyns have a duty to defend\nIlia's faithful; I will do all I can.
Expand the search outside the village!\nLeave no stone unturned!
I bring ill news: We found a child's\nribbon at the entrance to the forest.
The poor thing must have gone inside!
Assemble a search party at once.\nSplit up and investigate every inch\nof that forest!
Er, I'm afraid we can't enter the forest.
Because that forest is where this\ndiocese's guardian dragon lives.
We have no place entering it.
But what of my granddaughter?!\nWhat will happen to her?!
I'm afraid all we can do is wait for her\nto return and let Ilia's will be done.
You cannot! The Church's creed is to\nrespect Ilia and dragonkind!
We knights of the Church need follow that\nmore than any! We cannot invade a\ndragon's territory!
You seem to be forgetting the second half\nof the creed. Do we not also have a duty\nto guide people to prosperity?
Ilia's faithful are not dragons,\nbut people!

The Ilian Church exists for the sake of
mankind—and Ilia's true wish is the
heresy of saving them, not the belief
they should be left to die!
...So he ended up entering the forest.
And in so doing, saved my granddaughter.
But his actions earned\nthe ire of the dragon.
Leaving him no choice\nbut to defend himself.
The moment he returned from the forest,\nhe was seized by the other Paladyns.
They branded him a heretic for harming\nthat dragon, so they did!
Tobias is a hero who saved a child,\nand any church that calls him a\nheretic is sorely mistaken!
Oh, the Church is real fine when it comes\nto preachin', but when do they actually\nsave anyone?!
Enough of that now.\nYou are in the presence of a Paladyn!
It's like we don't even understand\nthe teachings of Ilia no more.
We pray and we pray, but none of us\nactually think it'll do much good.
Until the moment he was taken away,\nTobias told us to believe in her. And yet...
(I knew he was no heretic! Yes, he took up\nhis blade to defend these people, but his\nheart was always with the Goddess.)

(If he had left that child to her fate, these
people would have resented the Church,
leading to a repeat of what happened
in the Belitz diocese.)
(Tobias tried to protect these people AND\ntheir faith—which makes my path clear!)
If it comes to it, we'll take up arms\nto go and rescue him!
I fear the use of force will only\nmake his predicament worse.
I think I know a way to save him...\nbut to do it, I need your help.
Oh ho! Perhaps Tobias was right after all!
Your arrival was clearly ordained by Ilia,\nwhich means she hasn't abandoned us!
Help him, good Paladyn! Help Tobias!
I shall. Now permit me to explain\nmy plan, if you would...
Tobias's trial is going to take place\nearlier than planned!
